div.p:
It should be noted, moreover, that in order to discern whether a war is just or unjust,
one must consider the authority, the disposition, the intention,
the condition, the merit, and the cause.
The disposition and the authority must be considered in the person declaring the war;
the condition and the intention in the person waging the war;
the merit in the person enduring the war;
and the cause in the person for whom the war is waged.
